After first planning to remove the Daunte Wright memorial in a residential neighborhood, Brooklyn Center city officials have agreed to leave it there and work on creating a permanent memorial at the intersection where Wright died last April. Aubrey and Katie Wright, along with attorney Jeff Storms, met with City Manager Reggie Edwards on Tuesday to discuss plans for the memorial to their son just days after Edwards notified them and memorial caretakers that the city this week planned to reopen the sidewalk at 63rd Avenue and Kathrene Drive. You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
